This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the task of recommending personalized playlists of relevant tracks to listeners. It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves analyzing user preferences and behavior to generate recommendations. Additionally, it could be categorized under the Systems and Control (cs.SYS) sub-category as it involves designing and evaluating a recommender system algorithm. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as matrix factorization and Bayesian Personalized Ranking, which could place it under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, it could be categorized under the Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) sub-category as it deals with the task of recommending music playlists.
